
  Name:  fscanf
  
  #include <stdio.h>
  int fscanf(FILE *stream, const char *format, . . .);
          
  The fscanf( ) function works exactly like the scanf( ) function
  except that it reads the information from the stream specified 
  by stream instead of stdin .
  
  Example:

  char str[80];
  float f;
  fscanf(fp, "%s%f", str, &f);
  
  Related Functions:  scanf and fprintf

